messages.message:
Closing this thread in case it's of help to someone coming here later -- this was fixed after we ran the account service locally.

Provisioner probably ran into issues trying to run the service, and they were not surfaced as the service was still in running state based on the status.

For anyone who runs into this - you can check if account service is correctly running with provisioner. You can also fall back on the old-school way of running the service with `make clean build runlocal`
